sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client<br/>(Dashboard/Pipeline)
    participant IstioGW as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proxy as model-registry proxy<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as MySQL/PostgreSQL<br/>3306/5432 TCP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as model-registry controller<br/>8081/TCP HTTP
    participant KServe as KServe Runtime<br/>(Init Container)
    participant StorageInit as mr-storage-initializer
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: Client Creates a Registered Model

    Client->>IstioGW: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+, Session/Token
    IstioGW->>Proxy: Forward via VirtualService<br/>HTTP, Istio mTLS
    Proxy->>DB: INSERT model metadata<br/>SQL, Optional TLS 1.2+<br/>Username/Password
    DB-->>Proxy: Success
    Proxy-->>IstioGW: 201 Created (JSON)
    IstioGW-->>Client: Response

    Note over K8sAPI,DB: Flow 2: InferenceService Reconciliation

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch notification<br/>InferenceService created/updated<br/>HTTP/2, TLS, SA Token
    Controller->>Proxy: GET/POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/*<br/>HTTP 8080, Bearer Token (optional)
    Proxy->>DB: Query/Update metadata<br/>SQL, Optional TLS 1.2+
    DB-->>Proxy: Result
    Proxy-->>Controller: JSON Response
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update InferenceService labels<br/>HTTPS 443, TLS, SA Token

    Note over KServe,S3: Flow 3: KServe Storage Initialization

    KServe->>StorageInit: model-registry:// URI<br/>(init-container)
    StorageInit->>Proxy: GET model artifact location<br/>HTTP 8080
    Proxy-->>StorageInit: Artifact URI (S3/GCS path)
    StorageInit->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS 443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Provider credentials
    S3-->>StorageInit: Model artifacts
    StorageInit-->>KServe: Model ready
